{"key":"post-10855367","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10855367</id>\n<content>You don't mist for humidity.&amp;nbsp; That's the job for perlite, and you need twice as much as you have.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You mist to replace the lost moisture from your substrates due to the fresh air exchange.&amp;nbsp; The answer is 'mist as required' and nobody can say how many times per day.&amp;nbsp; You'll have to eyeball your cakes and if they're dry, it's time to mist.&amp;nbsp; If not, don't.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10857398</next>\n<prev>10855349</prev>\n<first>10854326</first>\n<last>10857998</last>\n<when>1250214418</when>\n<utime>08/14/09 04:46 AM</utime>\n</post>"}